<br>
First off, just keep your eyes open for folks who interest you in RP, and your eyes shut for folks who don't interest you.  If someone's spoiling things for you by being a nitwit, /ignore's a good tool.  (Well, if they're not breaking rules, which has its own set of /report /petition.)  Experiment with fun little quirks that give you and those around you a sense of who your character is, and don't be afraid to travel.  Young wood elves can find some very fun RP, but they can also find RP hampered severely by those in GFay.  It seems to go through phases.<br>
<br>
Oh, and learn languages when you can, especially human.  You can RP via emotes, but it's a lot more fun if you can chat, too! <p><p align="center">
