<br>
1. Forage alot. Not buying food and water is good, plus you can practice some tradeskills nearly for free with foraged stuff. There are alot of non-foraging tradeskillers who might be interested in stacks of roots and veggies and rabbits, too.<br>
<br>
2. Do your newbie armor quests. They are very nice - decent AC, plus stat bonuses on every bit. And they are a lovely, soothing green.<br>
<br>
3. Bone chips to the dwarves in Kaladim. Ditto for Crushbone belts. Those two things will outfit you in basic gear quickly, get you nice exp, and enough spell money to start with.<br>
<br>
4. Do the rusty weapon quest in the Druid guild - it can get you a tarnished scimitar, which is how you can start work on your 1HS skill. The pixie dust quest in the Ranger guild can get you rawhide armor - which is worth it, too.<br>
<br>
5. All sorts of rats (from the level 1 large rats to the teen-level plague rats) in Steamfont have a chance of dropping Plague Rat Tails, which sell for about a plat each to merchants. There's some low-level spell money.<br>
<br>
6. Once the butcherblock dwarven newbie quests are live (I know they are on Test, don't know if they are on FV yet, haven't checked), HUNT GOBLINS! Their heads and their blood are about 4pp each to a merchant. There's more spell money. Plus the dwarves will start loving you.<br>
<br>
7. There are excellent places other than Faydark and Crushbone to hunt at the lower levels. If you like those places, great! If you don't, you aren't stuck there - Steamfont and Butcherblock can both take you comfortably into the high teens, and they are less overcrowded/prone to trains/loud.<br>
